---
const description =
  'AI platform engineer at Atlassian working on reliable agent runtimes and secure execution.';
const canonicalUrl = new URL('/resume/', Astro.site);
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" class="resume-document">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <title>Alexander Sumer - Resume</title>
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonicalUrl.href} />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin="anonymous" />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lato:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,700;0,900;1,300;1,400&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />

    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Alexander Sumer - Resume" />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:url" content={canonicalUrl.href} />
    <meta property="og:image" content={new URL('/og-image.jpg', Astro.site).href} />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Alexander Sumer" />
  </head>
  <body class="resume-page">
    <header class="h">
      <h1 class="h-name">Alexander Sumer</h1>
      <div class="h-sub">Sydney, NSW, Australia</div>
      <div class="h-contact">
        <a href="https://github.com/alexandersumer">github.com/alexandersumer</a>
        <span class="d">·</span>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexandersumer">linkedin.com/in/alexandersumer</a>
      </div>
      <div class="h-pos">{description}</div>
    </header>

    <section class="s">
      <h2 class="s-title">Experience</h2>

      <div class="e">
        <div class="e-row">
          <span class="e-org">Atlassian</span>
          <span class="e-loc">Sydney, Australia</span>
        </div>
        <div class="e-row">
          <span class="e-role">Senior Machine Learning Systems Engineer, AI Platform</span>
          <span class="e-date">Jul 2025 – Present</span>
        </div>
        <div class="e-row">
          <span class="e-role">Senior Engineer, Jira Platform</span>
          <span class="e-date">Mar 2024 – Jun 2025</span>
        </div>
        <div class="e-row">
          <span class="e-role">Earlier Jira Platform roles: Engineer, Graduate &amp; Intern</span>
          <span class="e-date">Nov 2019 – Feb 2024</span>
        </div>
        <p class="e-summary">
          Merged 1,903 PRs in FY26, the most at Atlassian, by directing and reviewing coding agents.
          Delivered 3 cross-team talks and workshops on effective coding-agent use. Received 5 Big
          Kudos, including one for each talk and 2 Fix-of-the-Week awards from Atlassian's CTO of AI
          and Teamwork.
        </p>
        <ul class="b">
          <li class="proj">
            <strong>Agent Platform:</strong> On a small tiger team, built a platform for teams to define,
            publish, and run managed agents. Led the runtime and persistence work, including durable sessions,
            recovery, and hibernation. Shipped TypeScript, JVM, Python, and Rust SDKs against a shared
            contract and took the versioned agent and plugin catalog to production.
          </li>
          <li class="proj">
            <strong>Agent Sandbox:</strong> Owned the shared sandbox runtime used by three AI products.
            Integrated persistent workspaces and session hibernation, and hardened authorization and readiness
            checks. Replaced a legacy runtime that lacked persistent workspaces and relied on linear namespace
            scans, enabling agents to create files and resume work across sessions.
          </li>
          <li class="proj">
            <strong>AI Platform Reliability:</strong> Led reliability improvements across Atlassian's
            AI products. Reduced average incident recovery time from 10 hours to 1 hour, moved a synchronous
            Kotlin service to Coroutines, and cut redundant network calls by 90% with shared HTTP clients
            and two-tier caching.
          </li>
          <li class="proj">
            <strong>Autonomous Browser Agent:</strong> Led 5 engineers building a Gemini-powered browser
            agent. Designed warm pools for sub-second startup, signed routing, and per-session isolation.
            The system topped internal evaluations and completed complex compliance workflows end-to-end.
          </li>
          <li class="proj">
            <strong>Jira Issue Service:</strong> Built a Jira platform service from inception that achieved
            99.999% reliability. Added a persistence layer and at-least-once event stream, improved P90
            latency 20× by parallelizing authorization, and cut P99 latency from 10s to 200ms for the
            largest customers.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="earlier">
        <div class="earlier-head">
          <strong>Sympli</strong> · Developer · Oct 2018 – Jul 2019
        </div>
        <div class="earlier-note">
          Built a server-side form generator (JSON → React) for electronic real estate transactions,
          a serverless healthcheck service (Lambda, SNS), and introduced unit testing standards
          across the team.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="earlier">
        <div class="earlier-head">
          <strong>WiseTech Global</strong> · Associate Developer · Aug 2017 – Sep 2018
        </div>
        <div class="earlier-note">
          Built a coordinate-based distance/time matrix API with algorithm selection based on graph
          structure. Replaced SQL literals with table-valued parameters for a 4× query performance
          improvement.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="s">
      <h2 class="s-title">Education</h2>
      <div class="e">
        <div class="e-row">
          <span class="e-org">University of New South Wales</span>
          <span class="e-loc">Sydney, Australia</span>
        </div>
        <div class="e-row">
          <span class="e-role">Bachelor of Computer Science</span>
          <span class="e-date">Jul 2016 – May 2020</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="b">
          <li>Teaching assistant for COMP2521 Algorithms and Data Structures.</li>
          <li>
            Volunteer C++ developer on rUNSWift (UNSW SPL robotics team). Worked on ball detection
            using the Kalman filter.
          </li>
          <li>Competitive programming: 2017 ANZAC Round 2, 2018 NZPC, weekly ACM ICPC training.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="s">
      <h2 class="s-title">Skills &amp; Interests</h2>
      <div class="sk">
        <span class="sk-l">Technical focus</span>
        <span class="sk-v"
          >Agent platforms, coding agents, multi-agent orchestration, secure sandboxing, distributed
          systems</span
        >
        <span class="sk-l">Interests</span>
        <span class="sk-v"
          >Painting and the arts, reading and writing, fitness, volleyball, road trips</span
        >
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>

<style is:global>
  @page {
    size: letter;
    margin: 10mm 14mm;
  }

  .resume-document,
  .resume-document *,
  .resume-document *::before,
  .resume-document *::after {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .resume-document {
    background: #f0f0f0;
    print-color-adjust: exact;
    -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
  }

  .resume-page {
    max-width: 215.9mm;
    margin: 48px auto;
    padding: 10mm 14mm;
    background: #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgb(0 0 0 / 15%);
    color: #2b2b2b;
    font-family:
      'Lato',
      -apple-system,
      BlinkMacSystemFont,
      'Segoe UI',
      Helvetica,
      Arial,
      sans-serif;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.4;
    -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  .resume-page a {
    color: #2563eb;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .resume-page a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .h {
    padding-bottom: 1.5mm;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .h-name {
    color: #1a1a1a;
    font-size: 25pt;
    font-weight: 300;
    letter-spacing: 2.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .h-sub {
    margin-top: 0.3mm;
    color: #888;
    font-size: 9pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.3px;
  }

  .h-contact {
    margin-top: 0.8mm;
    color: #444;
    font-size: 8.5pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.2px;
  }

  .h-contact a {
    color: #444;
  }

  .h-contact .d {
    display: inline;
    margin: 0 6px;
    color: #bbb;
  }

  .h-pos {
    max-width: 540px;
    margin: 0.8mm auto 0;
    color: #555;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .s {
    margin-top: 3mm;
  }

  .s-title {
    margin-bottom: 2mm;
    padding-bottom: 1.5mm;
    border-bottom: 1.5px solid #1a1a1a;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .e {
    margin-bottom: 2.5mm;
  }

  .e:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .e-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  .e-org {
    color: #1a1a1a;
    font-size: 10.5pt;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .e-loc {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-left: 12px;
    color: #666;
    font-size: 8.5pt;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .e-role {
    margin-top: 0.3mm;
    color: #444;
    font-size: 8.5pt;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .e-date {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-left: 12px;
    color: #666;
    font-size: 8.5pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .e-summary {
    margin-top: 1mm;
  }

  ul.b {
    margin-top: 1mm;
    padding-left: 14px;
    list-style: none;
  }

  ul.b li {
    position: relative;
    color: #2b2b2b;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  ul.b li + li {
    margin-top: 0.8mm;
  }

  ul.b li.proj {
    margin-top: 1.5mm;
  }

  ul.b li::before {
    position: absolute;
    left: -14px;
    color: #999;
    content: '–';
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  ul.b li strong {
    color: #1a1a1a;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .earlier {
    margin-top: 1.5mm;
  }

  .earlier-head {
    color: #444;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
  }

  .earlier-head strong {
    color: #1a1a1a;
  }

  .earlier-note {
    margin-top: 0.3mm;
    padding-left: 14px;
    color: #555;
    font-size: 9pt;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .sk {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 1.5mm 12px;
    margin-top: 1mm;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
  }

  .sk-l {
    color: #1a1a1a;
    font-weight: 700;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .sk-v {
    color: #2b2b2b;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
    .resume-page {
      max-width: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 24px 18px;
      box-shadow: none;
    }

    .h-name {
      font-size: 20pt;
      letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    }

    .h-contact {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 2px;
    }

    .h-contact .d {
      display: none;
    }

    .e-row {
      display: block;
    }

    .e-loc,
    .e-date {
      display: block;
      margin: 0.2mm 0 0;
      white-space: normal;
    }

    .sk {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.5mm;
    }

    .sk-v + .sk-l {
      margin-top: 1mm;
    }
  }

  @media print {
    .resume-document {
      background: #fff;
    }

    .resume-page {
      max-width: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-shadow: none;
    }

    .resume-page a {
      color: #2563eb !important;
    }

    .s {
      break-inside: avoid;
    }
  }
</style>
